article.description: Buffalo pulls away from Robert Morris 74-56.
article.headline: Buffalo pulls away from Robert Morris 74-56.
article.linkText: Buffalo pulls away from Robert Morris 74-56.
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Justin Moss scored 20 points and grabbed 11 rebounds and Buffalo wrapped up a six-game road trip with a 74-59 win over Robert Morris on Sunday. The unusual schedule was caused when Montana State couldn't get to Buffalo for a game on Nov. 21. The Bulls (5-2) also got 14 points from Shannon Evans, 12 from Will Regan and 11 from Jarryn Skeete. Evans and Skeete also had five assists apiece as Buffalo had 16 assists on 25 baskets. Marcquise Reed had 18 points for Robert Morris (2-6), which had 24 turnovers and went 4 of 20 from 3-point range. A 3-pointer by Regan and Rodell Wigginton's dunk at 7:37 made it 22-10 for the Bulls, who eventually pushed the lead to 15 before settling for a 33-23 advantage at halftime. The Colonials got within seven but Skeete sandwiched two 3's around a Wigginton dunk that made it 49-31 with 12:23 to play.
